02:07:16,565 --> 02:07:21,667
I mean, this is probably an appropriate time to start looking at the garage again in Medford square.

1712
02:07:22,387 --> 02:07:23,768
Um, the money is set aside.

1713
02:07:24,028 --> 02:07:26,389
State representative has it in the bond bill.

1714
02:07:27,129 --> 02:07:31,271
And, um, I think that this is the appropriate time to actually start talking about it again.

1715
02:07:32,211 --> 02:07:32,311
Um,

1716
02:07:33,994 --> 02:07:38,435
There is a need for longer-term business parking within the square.

1717
02:07:39,296 --> 02:07:58,482
So, I think the administration should take it under consideration, at least at this point, because the business owners that are complaining about not having spots, if there are additional spots that are allocated for long-term parking, and as I said in the past, the administration, it was another one of those issues that they just never brought forward.

1718
02:07:59,002 --> 02:08:01,983
They talked about it, and this and that, and the council talked about it,

1719
02:08:02,307 --> 02:08:07,750
But there has not been a proposal for the garage that's been before us for a vote for funding.

1720
02:08:08,250 --> 02:08:19,275
And as I said, State Rep Donato has worked tirelessly to get funding in the transportation bond bill for that specific purpose, as well as other money that was set aside by, I believe, the previous administration.

1721
02:08:19,295 --> 02:08:20,096
Point of clarification.

1722
02:08:20,116 --> 02:08:20,636
Point of clarification.

1723
02:08:20,656 --> 02:08:20,936
Council Penta.

1724
02:08:20,956 --> 02:08:30,721
The reason that money got into the bond bill is when the mayor knew that three members of the council weren't going to vote for it, he went to Representative Donato, who never came to us, to explain that they were putting that money into the bond bill.

1725
02:08:31,418 --> 02:08:36,662
So there was no understanding of that money going in by any vote of this council one way or the other.

1726
02:08:36,682 --> 02:08:37,643
Did I say that?

1727
02:08:39,144 --> 02:08:40,145
Yes, you didn't say that.

1728
02:08:40,365 --> 02:08:41,045
I did not say that.

1729
02:08:41,426 --> 02:08:45,809
All I said was in the transportation bond bill, there's $3 million set aside.

1730
02:08:45,829 --> 02:08:50,412
$8 million, Councilor Caviello said.

1731
02:08:50,432 --> 02:09:00,460
I'm not exactly sure on the figure, but the bottom line is I think as one member of this council, there is a need for it.

1732
02:09:01,014 --> 02:09:05,296
And we haven't had the opportunity to take a formal vote, whether we're for or against it.

1733
02:09:05,796 --> 02:09:23,262
And as I said, I'm urging the administration to bring it forward and finally give the people of Medford Square, the neighbors, the business owners, an opportunity to come down here and be heard, as people were given the opportunity to come down in the Brooks Estates, the new science labs, and the list goes on and on and on.

1734
02:09:23,802 --> 02:09:27,303
Jot the Course, which was brought forward by the McGlynn administration.

1735
02:09:28,183 --> 02:09:29,724
This was part of it originally, I believe.

1736
02:09:30,165 --> 02:09:31,365
And it just never came to a vote.

1737
02:09:31,565 --> 02:09:37,507
So I think that we owe it at least to the business owners to take a long, serious look at it.

1738
02:09:38,047 --> 02:09:48,030
And unfortunately, the people out there, the farmer garage was built under the old farmer government, where it was the city council and the city managers back in, I want to say the 80s.

1739
02:09:48,490 --> 02:09:55,172
And I'm sure Mayor McGlynn still has the plaque from the garage when it fell down with the names on it.

1740
02:09:55,632 --> 02:09:58,173
But with that being said, it's

1741
02:09:59,842 --> 02:10:01,243
I think it's long overdue.

1742
02:10:01,744 --> 02:10:03,666
And I, as one member of this council do support it.

1743
02:10:03,826 --> 02:10:07,790
And I would hope that it at least entertain it and give the people the opportunity to be heard.

1744
02:10:08,350 --> 02:10:08,691
Thank you.

1745
02:10:08,711 --> 02:10:11,033
Um, thank you chief for answering our questions.

1746
02:10:11,073 --> 02:10:14,636
Again, some questions resolved council Penta chief.

1747
02:10:14,756 --> 02:10:15,457
One last question.

1748
02:10:15,637 --> 02:10:19,941
And, um, the hours of operation have now been changed from eight to six.

1749
02:10:20,242 --> 02:10:20,722
That's correct.

1750
02:10:20,862 --> 02:10:21,783
Monday through Saturday.

1751
02:10:22,003 --> 02:10:22,304
Correct.

1752
02:10:22,424 --> 02:10:24,646
Can you tell me why the office is not open on a Saturday?

1753
02:10:27,307 --> 02:10:27,707
I don't know.

1754
02:10:28,428 --> 02:10:31,270
I think they try to follow city hall hours.

1755
02:10:31,990 --> 02:10:33,411
City hall is not the parking clerk.

1756
02:10:33,771 --> 02:10:37,094
They're open late on Wednesday night.

1757
02:10:37,154 --> 02:10:37,894
It doesn't work that way.

1758
02:10:37,914 --> 02:10:41,917
There are people that on Saturday is the only day they can make this appointment or see them or whatever it might be.

1759
02:10:42,818 --> 02:10:43,538
This is not fair.

1760
02:10:43,558 --> 02:10:44,399
It's another issue.

1761
02:10:44,419 --> 02:10:50,483
If you can make a notation, ask them to be open on Saturday from 8 to 6, just like they are every other day.

1762
02:10:51,648 --> 02:10:57,496
You know, if they're good enough to give out the tickets, they should be good enough to hear their complaints on the same days that they give out their tickets.

1763
02:10:58,718 --> 02:10:59,318
Madam President.

1764
02:11:00,921 --> 02:11:03,004
If I may too, I'd just like to go on record.

1765
02:11:04,749 --> 02:11:21,970
I know there is some frustration by some of the members of the Ticket Enforcement Unit, but there are several members of working for that company that are good, long-standing Medford families, Medford residents, and I think they're doing a fine and admirable job.

1766
02:11:22,590 --> 02:11:26,192
You call that office, we all know who works up in the office.

1767
02:11:26,912 --> 02:11:31,474
A Medford gal and very friendly, two Medford gals, I didn't know the other one.

1768
02:11:31,934 --> 02:11:39,396
And then one of the enforcement officers is a Medford young man that grew up here in our community.

1769
02:11:39,857 --> 02:11:43,538
So the ones that at least live in this community are taking pride in their work.

1770
02:11:44,298 --> 02:11:46,379
And I just want the record to reflect that.

1771
02:11:51,668 --> 02:11:58,374
Motion to receive in place on file and hopefully chief will get us, you know, ask those questions for us, get us those answers.

1772
02:11:59,155 --> 02:11:59,795
All those in favor.

1773
02:12:00,296 --> 02:12:00,896
All those opposed.

1774
02:12:01,397 --> 02:12:01,997
It passes.

1775
02:12:02,918 --> 02:12:03,278
Thank you.

1776
02:12:03,819 --> 02:12:05,120
Motion to revert back to regular.

1777
02:12:05,140 --> 02:12:06,381
Could I just ask one question?

1778
02:12:06,421 --> 02:12:06,942
I'm sorry.

1779
02:12:07,122 --> 02:12:08,483
I just, I'm just curious.

1780
02:12:09,304 --> 02:12:17,271
I know you have the year for the public concerns and all the complaints, but I'm not hearing all the complaints.

1781
02:12:17,908 --> 02:12:19,929
on the parking that I did in the very beginning.

1782
02:12:20,169 --> 02:12:24,031
I'm wondering, are you hearing anything positive?

1783
02:12:24,511 --> 02:12:28,193
Because I've been hearing from some merchants that this is beginning to work.

1784
02:12:29,394 --> 02:12:30,575
I've been hearing some positives.

1785
02:12:31,755 --> 02:12:32,536
I hear some positives.

1786
02:12:33,356 --> 02:12:41,100
It's obvious that we need to round off the rough edges, but I just want to know, are you hearing any of the good things?

1787
02:12:41,160 --> 02:12:44,002
Because sometimes I think the silent majority is out there.

1788
02:12:44,042 --> 02:12:46,783
No one likes someone to come up and put a ticket on their windshield.

1789
02:12:47,332 --> 02:12:52,794
whether you're a sworn police officer or you're a civilian, they don't want the tickets so they're going to complain.

1790
02:12:55,434 --> 02:12:56,115
Councillor Camuso.

1791
02:12:56,515 --> 02:13:01,676
The one thing that's been unanimous amongst the people that I talk to is they all look forward to Sunday.

1792
02:13:03,497 --> 02:13:04,337
The day of rest.

1793
02:13:04,777 --> 02:13:14,360
I think, on a serious note though, we brought it up a few weeks ago, the holiday has to be straightened out and it has to be a lot of public output because

1794
02:13:15,088 --> 02:13:18,910
There were people on Patriots Day, and you weren't here for the meeting, but people on Patriots Day were getting tickets.

1795
02:13:18,930 --> 02:13:24,853
Now, I know the company did write by it, but it has to be unison.

1796
02:13:24,893 --> 02:13:27,394
Is it the federal calendar, or is it the state calendar?

1797
02:13:27,814 --> 02:13:35,178
I think it should be the state calendar, because how can you justify having City Hall closed and the schools closed, but still be able to get a ticket?

1798
02:13:35,678 --> 02:13:38,240
And rubbish delivery doesn't get picked up, like Councilor Pender said.

1799
02:13:38,560 --> 02:13:40,481
It should be all holidays on both schedules.

1800
02:13:40,661 --> 02:13:41,681
I think it was corrected.

1801
02:13:43,124 --> 02:13:43,304
Ms.

1802
02:13:43,324 --> 02:13:46,907
Burke gave them the list of holidays, and I think it was all of them.

1803
02:13:48,168 --> 02:13:53,012
I'm not sure if Bunker Hill Day fit in that category, but all the others did.

1804
02:13:53,372 --> 02:13:56,315
Bunker Hill Day, though, City Hall is closed, so it should be closed.

1805
02:13:57,395 --> 02:13:57,656
I agree.

1806
02:13:57,676 --> 02:13:58,516
All right.

1807
02:13:58,757 --> 02:13:59,117
Thank you.

1808
02:13:59,277 --> 02:13:59,597
Thank you.

1809
02:13:59,737 --> 02:14:00,378
Thanks, Chief.

1810
02:14:03,340 --> 02:14:03,600
Yes.

1811
02:14:03,700 --> 02:14:11,727
Motions, orders, and resolutions 15-470 offered by Councilor Caviello be resolved with the Medford City Council, discuss the proposed

1812
02:14:12,157 --> 02:14:23,321
Proposed appeal of 198202 Harvard Street to change from a three-family to a non-conforming five-family in an already congested area with insufficient off-street parking.

1813
02:14:23,381 --> 02:14:24,221
Counselor Carviello.

1814
02:14:24,481 --> 02:14:25,321
Thank you, Madam President.

1815
02:14:25,722 --> 02:14:42,027
You know, Madam President, as the Ball Square station is getting closer to us, completion, people in that neighborhood are going to start seeing more and more of these conversions that are going to want to happen.

1816
02:14:42,750 --> 02:14:45,611
Property is selling at record prices up there right now.

1817
02:14:45,951 --> 02:14:49,033
South Memphis and the real estate market is on fire.

1818
02:14:49,653 --> 02:14:51,394
And people are starting to cash out now.

1819
02:14:52,314 --> 02:15:01,278
But I think the time has come where I think we need to sit down, maybe with the appeals board or somebody, to discuss all these that are going to come in.

1820
02:15:01,298 --> 02:15:05,760
I mean, here's somebody that wants to go from a three to a five on Harvard Street.

1821
02:15:06,280 --> 02:15:08,681
I mean, did the chief already leave?

1822
02:15:09,661 --> 02:15:10,322
Chief left already.

1823
02:15:12,427 --> 02:15:16,888
I mean, there's barely enough parking for the three-family there.

1824
02:15:17,108 --> 02:15:28,971
Never mind, you're going to add four more people, which might be four more cars, five more cars in an area that just cannot handle any more cars or any more people.

1825
02:15:29,951 --> 02:15:35,692
And I say, as these two families continue to sell, people are going to want to take the two, make it a three.

1826
02:15:36,072 --> 02:15:37,272
Three is going to want to go to a four.

1827
02:15:37,732 --> 02:15:40,013
I mean, Stern's Ave just sold for $8.90, a two-family.

1828
02:15:42,642 --> 02:15:45,484
to a person who works up at Tufts.

1829
02:15:45,564 --> 02:15:54,428
It's only a matter of time before the gentleman's on it, before the appeals board, that's going to want to tear that down, or make that a fire family.

1830
02:15:55,789 --> 02:16:06,174
So I say, I think the time has come where we need to send a message to the appeal boards that next week, you better look hard and fast on these,

1831
02:16:09,400 --> 02:16:13,181
As they say, as fast as they start coming, as the train gets closer, they're going to come further.

1832
02:16:13,521 --> 02:16:16,202
And once it gets over the college, you're going to see the hillside.

1833
02:16:16,242 --> 02:16:18,382
I mean, can you fit a little car on the hillside?

1834
02:16:18,402 --> 02:16:19,923
Or can you fit another apartment on the hillside?

1835
02:16:20,623 --> 02:16:22,463
I mean, these people, I mean, listen, it's good.

1836
02:16:23,023 --> 02:16:25,624
It's good for the, you know, if you want to cash out, it's good.

1837
02:16:25,664 --> 02:16:28,125
But we're fast losing our neighborhoods.

1838
02:16:28,825 --> 02:16:29,825
There'll be no more neighborhoods.

1839
02:16:30,225 --> 02:16:32,826
There'll be just, we'll be a city of transients.

1840
02:16:33,026 --> 02:16:36,347
That's why people come in, students, and I say, I mean,

1841
02:16:37,923 --> 02:16:41,785
There's five generations of my family that have been in this city.

1842
02:16:43,866 --> 02:16:47,548
That won't be happening much if this continues at this pace.

1843
02:16:48,468 --> 02:16:51,169
Would you like to make a recommendation to the Board of Appeals?

1844
02:16:51,269 --> 02:16:54,251
Yes, I plan on going to this meeting next week also during that one.

1845
02:16:54,271 --> 02:16:56,372
You want to make a recommendation?

1846
02:16:56,392 --> 02:17:07,497
I want to make a recommendation that they either maybe look at maybe some type of moratorium or some type of, before they approve,

1847
02:17:08,863 --> 02:17:14,546
Any more of these, maybe we should be kept more in the loop in this.

1848
02:17:15,006 --> 02:17:22,350
Recommend that the Board of Appeals put a moratorium until the matter is discussed with the City Council?

1849
02:17:22,710 --> 02:17:22,910
Yes.

1850
02:17:26,712 --> 02:17:27,433
Councilor Camuso.

1851
02:17:27,573 --> 02:17:27,913
Thank you.

1852
02:17:29,670 --> 02:17:40,218
I agree with a lot of the sentiments of Councillor Caviello, but I also know there are a lot of two and three families that have significant amount of parking right on their own property.

1853
02:17:40,859 --> 02:17:44,462
And this is a new way of life.

1854
02:17:44,902 --> 02:17:46,363
People don't want the big homes anymore.

1855
02:17:46,403 --> 02:17:48,605
They want to buy a smaller condominium.

1856
02:17:49,786 --> 02:17:52,668
So I just think the Board of Appeals has to look at each individual cases.

1857
02:17:53,489 --> 02:17:57,892
Similar to a few years ago when the Meadow Glen Mall sign came up, and I'm not far of those big signs.

1858
02:17:58,234 --> 02:18:01,816
But in certain areas, I think they're actually good and they bring business.

1859
02:18:02,497 --> 02:18:11,843
But to tell someone that there's a moratorium in place, and if they have 7,500 square feet and they can fit the appropriate parking and-.

1860
02:18:12,743 --> 02:18:21,089
Maybe moratorium might be the wrong word, but at least we look at the rules that go with the granting of these

1861
02:18:23,770 --> 02:18:24,190
changes.

1862
02:18:24,570 --> 02:18:29,492
But a lot of times the conversions, I think the conversions and the board of appeals are two separate things.

1863
02:18:30,292 --> 02:18:39,796
Um, a lot of times you don't even have to go to the board of appeals to convert to a, if you already own a two family, it's more or less just going to the building department and condo eyes in it.

1864
02:18:39,936 --> 02:18:43,357
And you have to have converting two to two, two to five.

1865
02:18:43,637 --> 02:18:47,118
I mean, two is going to go to three, three is going to go to four.

1866
02:18:47,438 --> 02:18:52,920
I mean, but some of them, a three family is going to could have six cars in there.

1867
02:18:53,182 --> 02:18:53,942
But I understand that.

1868
02:18:54,002 --> 02:19:03,345
But also, there are some buildings throughout our community that are currently zoned for more than the units that they have.

1869
02:19:03,425 --> 02:19:05,585
They may have a zoning for a six-family.

1870
02:19:05,945 --> 02:19:10,927
At the end of Irving Street, at the corner of Irving and Placestead, you've got six or seven units in that building.

1871
02:19:11,527 --> 02:19:12,427
Now, is it appropriate?

1872
02:19:13,707 --> 02:19:14,948
But it's conforming use.

1873
02:19:15,328 --> 02:19:16,208
It's a conforming use.

1874
02:19:16,837 --> 02:19:26,303
And I agree with you that we have to actually take a long, hard look at it, but I think we have to leave it in the Board of Appeals hands, and they have to look at it individually.

1875
02:19:26,723 --> 02:19:34,949
Because there are certain lots and properties within the community that take a blighted area, for instance.

1876
02:19:35,949 --> 02:19:45,596
You'd rather have maybe a three or four family than the one family that's run as a rental place.

1877
02:19:46,547 --> 02:20:00,635
It's, I think, I just think the Board of Appeals right now is in a total, it's a good, it's a good, not it's a good, it's the only avenue where they can go and look at it realistically, too.

1878
02:20:01,656 --> 02:20:10,521
They are very, I'd say that they deny more than they approve developments and conversions in the city.

1879
02:20:11,061 --> 02:20:12,722
I mean, I'd like to know the statistics on it, too,

1880
02:20:14,210 --> 02:20:17,552
How many of these properties have actually made it to the Board of Appeals and were approved?

1881
02:20:17,572 --> 02:20:18,972
I don't know, sir.

1882
02:20:19,593 --> 02:20:21,173
I mean, that's something that I'd like to know.

1883
02:20:23,374 --> 02:20:24,375
Councillor Penta.

1884
02:20:25,535 --> 02:20:32,739
I agree somewhat with Councillor Camuso, but, you know, the Board of Appeals has a statutory autonomy, so to speak, to make their own decisions.

1885
02:20:33,900 --> 02:20:40,323
But the council has a right to interject what its concerns might be in a particular neighbourhood or a particular section.

1886
02:20:41,343 --> 02:20:43,104
We can jump over to another location

1887
02:20:43,835 --> 02:20:51,717
It's on Winthrop Street, right opposite the gas station, where across the street they want to put 11 houses into a four-home unit area over there.

1888
02:20:51,737 --> 02:20:53,798
I mean, I don't know how they're going to do it, whatever it might be.

1889
02:20:54,518 --> 02:20:57,319
So that's a true encroachment in a particular neighborhood.

1890
02:20:57,339 --> 02:21:02,220
And if the residents don't want it, or they're not even aware of it because

1891
02:21:03,586 --> 02:21:08,730
They just don't either have the time to be bothered with it or to be involved with it.

1892
02:21:08,930 --> 02:21:14,335
I mean, you know, we do have a responsibility if something we feel needs to be communicated to any particular board.

1893
02:21:15,155 --> 02:21:20,439
You know, one of the benefits of getting all these notices when these board meetings are, we see what the agendas might be.

1894
02:21:20,499 --> 02:21:27,565
And some of these agendas have worked out for the purposes of having a council go to them and find out what's going on or express their interest.

1895
02:21:28,085 --> 02:21:31,788
Now, I know Councilor Caviello, this won't be the first time,

1896
02:21:32,468 --> 02:21:46,775
that he would have an interest at the Board of Appeals because, and rightfully so, he had an interest in a piece of property in the West Medford area where the legitimacy of why the building was being sold and what was going to be proposed to be put there was not one and the same.

1897
02:21:47,735 --> 02:21:52,698
And because of his interaction at the board and with the neighborhood, it helped resolve the problem.

1898
02:21:52,778 --> 02:21:59,421
So what was going to originally go up and what became after the fact did not really come to fruition.

1899
02:21:59,781 --> 02:22:02,062
And this might be a combination of the same thing.

1900
02:22:02,998 --> 02:22:05,681
I don't think anybody should be dissuaded from going to any meeting.

1901
02:22:06,081 --> 02:22:14,588
City Council, Board of Appeals, Public Health, Water and Soil Commission meeting, whatever it might be, because if you have your opinion, what difference does it make if you're an elected official or not?

1902
02:22:14,888 --> 02:22:26,658
And if you're going as an elected official expressing your opinion, but more importantly, people have expressed their concern to you, and that's the reason why you're going, well, to some degree, that adds some weight, I would assume, in any particular meeting.

1903
02:22:27,179 --> 02:22:30,942
That's what the board members are there for, to listen to all the opinions that people might have.

1904
02:22:31,528 --> 02:22:37,351
While they might be autonomous to make their own decision, they're not precluded from listening to other people's decisions.

1905
02:22:37,691 --> 02:22:38,252
I'll strike that.

1906
02:22:38,492 --> 02:22:41,654
They should not be precluded from listening to other people's decisions.

1907
02:22:42,054 --> 02:22:48,837
And that's the reason why we're elected, to listen to the people, hear what they have to say, go to a meeting if we want to go, and express our concerns.

1908
02:22:49,438 --> 02:22:51,239
So I agree with you, Councilor Caviello.

1909
02:22:51,699 --> 02:22:57,182
I don't think there's anything wrong with going to the meeting, expressing your opinion, even if it's contrary to all three members of the board.

1910
02:22:57,582 --> 02:22:59,003
At least you were there to say what you felt.

1911
02:23:01,295 --> 02:23:02,876
Councilor Caviello.

1912
02:23:03,417 --> 02:23:09,742
I just think it's time that we start protecting the integrity of our neighborhoods because otherwise they're going to cease to become neighborhoods.

1913
02:23:10,583 --> 02:23:13,605
Just going to become landing spots that people just move in and out.

1914
02:23:14,546 --> 02:23:15,026
Councilor Knight.

1915
02:23:15,767 --> 02:23:17,048
Madam President, thank you very much.

1916
02:23:17,108 --> 02:23:19,390
And thank you, Councilor Caviello for bringing this matter forward.

1917
02:23:20,110 --> 02:23:26,816
Although I understand your concerns, I do feel as though we need to really respect the autonomy of the Zoning Board of Appeals.

1918
02:23:27,440 --> 02:23:30,542
and their process should be undue from political interference and influence.

1919
02:23:31,622 --> 02:23:37,005
With that being said, I think that Councilor Caviello raises some great concerns about the situation that's going on there.

1920
02:23:37,805 --> 02:23:54,153
However, I think the proper course of action for this council to take would be to take a look at the current zoning ordinances and then maybe make recommendations to revise the current existing zoning ordinances that governs their operations as opposed to making recommendations to them that fall well within their scope and purview, Madam President.

1921
02:24:03,430 --> 02:24:04,651
Gene Martin, 10 Cummings Street.

1922
02:24:04,691 --> 02:24:05,011
Thank you.

1923
02:24:05,051 --> 02:24:07,292
And I'd like to agree with Mr. Carviello.

1924
02:24:08,633 --> 02:24:29,824
I mean, if you go to South Medford, they are crowded and maybe the answer is what Mr. Knight is saying is maybe I don't understand the process, but I do agree with Mr. Carviello's line of thought, which is that the crowded, the more crowded you become, the more cars on the street, the more stress it puts on the fire department, on the teachers, on the schools, you have more people.

1925
02:24:30,340 --> 02:24:33,227
more people that aren't related.

1926
02:24:34,129 --> 02:24:39,682
These two family houses that are getting rented have three non-relatives living in three different bedrooms.

1927
02:24:40,453 --> 02:24:42,254
They have three different cars per unit.

1928
02:24:43,795 --> 02:24:46,577
It just causes a lot of congestion, and I absolutely agree.

1929
02:24:46,597 --> 02:24:51,499
But maybe the right way to approach it is what Mr. Knight is saying, is to go in.

1930
02:24:51,980 --> 02:24:56,262
But the federal laws came in under 40B, and they get away with stuff anyway.

1931
02:24:56,362 --> 02:25:01,485
So, you know, the towers, domestic valley towers came in under 40B.

1932
02:25:01,525 --> 02:25:02,866
You had the 40B over there.

1933
02:25:03,426 --> 02:25:07,788
And when 40B came in, the towers, it was regulated very strongly for 30 years.

1934
02:25:08,909 --> 02:25:13,772
Once they got through their contract, now it's open to the general public.

1935
02:25:13,853 --> 02:25:17,795
And they have three, often three non-related people living in the same apartment.

1936
02:25:18,215 --> 02:25:22,078
And so, you know, you have a lot of, and they do, they're like roommates to each other.

1937
02:25:22,398 --> 02:25:23,319
They're not families.

1938
02:25:24,720 --> 02:25:26,561
In some areas that's okay, they can absorb it.

1939
02:25:27,742 --> 02:25:34,447
But certainly in certain parts of the city, there's a saturation point at which it becomes a problem.

1940
02:25:34,907 --> 02:25:36,448
And so I just want to make people aware of that.

1941
02:25:36,785 --> 02:25:42,271
If you're living in North Medford and you have a couple of houses that, you know, are party central, that's okay because it can be absorbed.

1942
02:25:42,571 --> 02:25:49,318
But if you have a couple of houses that are party central in South Medford, it's not going to be absorbed because there's already enough congestion.

1943
02:25:49,792 --> 02:25:50,973
The roads are more congested.

1944
02:25:50,993 --> 02:25:52,694
The cars make an impact.

1945
02:25:53,134 --> 02:25:58,677
And I'd just like to say that it puts a stress on the city, so it is a city issue.

1946
02:25:59,037 --> 02:26:06,202
And also, every week, I get a letter in the mail from a retailer, a real estate person, ready to sell my house.

1947
02:26:06,862 --> 02:26:07,662
I mean, it is hot.

1948
02:26:07,803 --> 02:26:08,623
The market is hot.

1949
02:26:09,063 --> 02:26:11,985
And I know that some people would love for me to move out of the city, but that's another story.

1950
02:26:12,465 --> 02:26:14,747
I'm just kidding.

1951
02:26:15,687 --> 02:26:16,208
Oh, thank you.

1952
02:26:16,948 --> 02:26:18,590
Keeping you guys as honest as I can.

1953
02:26:18,950 --> 02:26:26,736
But anyway, no, seriously, the market is hot, but that doesn't mean that we shouldn't have some kind of cap.

1954
02:26:27,197 --> 02:26:34,403
How we come about that, how we come to that conclusion on how to put controls on that is up for debate.

1955
02:26:34,883 --> 02:26:38,686
But the sentiment that he's talking about, I'm absolutely positive with.

1956
02:26:39,127 --> 02:26:39,387
Thank you.

1957
02:26:44,178 --> 02:26:45,639
Thank you, Madam Vice President.

1958
02:26:46,260 --> 02:26:55,706
As someone who lives in close proximity to the property in question, I have grave concerns for that as well.

1959
02:26:56,427 --> 02:27:02,591
And I'm intimately associated with the congestion we experience in South Medford.

1960
02:27:03,091 --> 02:27:12,538
I'm also intimately aware of so much of the change that's happened there and the changing real estate market there.

1961
02:27:13,352 --> 02:27:25,420
and the possibility that people of moderate to low income will find it difficult to live in that neighborhood, those people who are most in need of use of public transportation.

1962
02:27:27,101 --> 02:27:38,328
